a child earns its existence by the very measurement that audits it afterwards, so propose(node) asks lang/lower for the next level of human text with the ancestors and the settled siblings in the prompt and gets back leaf or a list of children, and lower(node) writes those children, deletes again every one whose removal changes no line of the build, renumbers the survivors and returns how many were proposed with the ones that lived, leaving nothing behind on disk if it raises;
